General Motors Corp said it is closingtwo plants for brief periods in March, placing 5,500 ontemporary layoff for up to two weeks.    The company said its Hamtramck Buick-Oldsmobile-Cadillacassembly plant in Detroit will be down from March 9 to March 16due to excess inventory of several models, placing 2,000workers on temporary layoff.    Its Chevrolet-Pontiac-GM of Canada assembly facility inNorwood, Ohio, will be closed two weeks from March 9 to 23 dueto material shortages, affecting 3,500. There is no change inthe 37,000 hourly workers out of work indefinitely. Reuter&#3;